\b Complaint Entry - Architecture\b0\par
Complaint Management System\par
\par

\b 1. Purpose\b0\par
Complaint Entry creates and manages customer complaints. It captures Fab Number, customer, address, category, and description. Complaints can be assigned to an engineer, reassigned, or closed from this module.\par
\par

\b 2. Main Files\b0\par
\bullet  new_complaint.php - list, add form, grid actions\par
\bullet  complaint_details.php - view one record\par
\bullet  assign_complaint.php - assign or reassign engineer\par
\bullet  closure_complaint.php - close complaint\par
\bullet  delete_complaint.php - delete record\par
\bullet  includes/complaint_datatable_helpers.php - grid helpers and permissions\par
\bullet  api/complaints_datatable.php - grid data\par
\bullet  api/complaint_fab_prefill.php - customer prefill by Fab Number\par
\par

\b 3. Shared Components\b0\par
\bullet  complaint_address_helpers.php - address fields\par
\bullet  complaint_category_helpers.php - complaint categories\par
\bullet  complaint_assignment_helpers.php - assign / reassign logic\par
\bullet  complaint_closure_helpers.php - closure logic\par
\bullet  ln_invoice_helpers.php / complaint_fab_prefill.js - Fab Number search and prefill\par
\bullet  rbac_access_helpers.php - permissions\par
\par

\b 4. Basic Flow\b0\par
\bullet  User opens Complaint Entry page\par
\bullet  Grid loads records from complaints table\par
\bullet  User adds a complaint with Fab Number and details\par
\bullet  Optional engineer assignment sets status to In Progress\par
\bullet  From grid, user can view, assign/reassign, close, or delete\par
\bullet  Assignment is stored in complaint_assignments\par
\par

\b 5. Database\b0\par
Main table: complaints\par
Related tables: complaint_assignments, complaint_closures, complaint_categories, ln_invoice_details\par
\par

\b 6. Permissions\b0\par
RBAC module: complaint-entry (view, add, delete, assign-complaint, reassign-complaint, closure)\par
}
